        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The windy wailer unleashes freezing wind filled with fearful wailing in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a [[/save ability=dexterity dc=15]] saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes 14 ([[/damage 4d6 type=cold]]) damage and is &amp;Reference[condition=frightened] for 1 minute. On a success, a creature takes half the damage and isn't &amp;Reference[condition=frightened]. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>A creature reduced to 0 hp by the windy wailer's Frightful Gale and later revived is permanently marked by a shock of white hair somewhere on its body.</p></div>",
