        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>When a creature that can see the windy wailer starts its turn within 30 feet of the wailer, the wailer can force it to make a [[/save ability=wisdom dc=15]] saving throw if the wailer isn't &amp;Reference[condition=incapacitated] and can see the creature. On a failure, a creature is &amp;Reference[condition=incapacitated] and its speed is reduced to 0 as it is mesmerized by the windy wailer.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Unless surprised, a creature can avert its eyes to avoid the saving throw at the start of its turn. If the creature does so, it can't see the windy wailer until the start of its next turn, when it can avert its eyes again. If the creature looks at the windy wailer in the meantime, it must immediately make the save.</p></div>",
